Note: eNCA only streamed The Duchess of Sussex's arrival. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Meghan Markle is in Johannesburg for the royal family's second leg of their South African tour. The Duke and Duchess of Sussex landed in Cape Town on 23 September. They kicked off their tour with a visit to The Justice Desk in Nyanga, where they spoke to young children who have been taught self-defence. The duchess has been in South Africa where she conducted various activities to raise awareness about women's rights.